  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Assessing the use of a T drain approach for an anastomotic leak after gastrointestinal
      surgery. The study's aim is to retrospectively assess the safety and benefits of this
      approach.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Assessing the use of a T drain approach for an anastomotic leak after gastrointestinal
      surgery. The T drain approach is inserting a latex t tube drain into the leak site of the
      anastomosed bowel and diverting the fecal matter. The study's aim is to retrospectively
      assess the safety and benefits of this approach.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
